      <entry xml:id="Slips_CampbeltownAMartinslips-idp161827296">
        <form>
          <orth>monais</orth>
        </form>
        <def>Notes: ‘coarse woolly twine used for setting up nets to ropes’. SND s.v. monish ‘orig. unascertained’.</def>
      </entry>
      <entry xml:id="Slips_CampbeltownAMartinslips-idp161828808">
        <form>
          <orth>bad</orth>
        </form>
        <def>Quotation: “We’ll try a bad.” Notes: ‘Shooting overboard 2 or 3 fathoms of net on a breezy night, as a test for presence of herring.’</def>
      </entry>
      <entry xml:id="Slips_CampbeltownAMartinslips-idp161830464">
        <form>
          <orth>ceannair</orth>
        </form>
        <def>Notes: the end of the bridle-rope, which is attached to the wing of the net. (Tarbert)</def>
